OL,3,CIncome tax to rise from 20% to 22% in
OL,4,Cthe Isle of Man
OL,6,FIncome tax in the Isle of Man is set
OL,7,Fto rise from 20% to 22%, with
OL,8,Fadditional funds to be reinvested into
OL,9,Fthe healthcare service.
OL,11,FThe tax rise is the first in 14 years
OL,12,Ffor the island, and will come into
OL,13,Feffect from 6th April 2024.
OL,15,FIt follows #46.8m of overspending
OL,16,Facross all government departments over
OL,17,Fthe past year.
