OL,3,CIncome tax to rise from 20% to 22% in
OL,4,Cthe Isle of Man
OL,6,FThe personal allowance will remain at
OL,7,F#14,500 for an individual and #29,000
OL,8,Ffor a jointly assessed couple. The
OL,9,Fmeasure, put in place at last year's
OL,10,Fbudget, whereby higher earners have
OL,11,Ftheir personal allowance reduced by #1
OL,12,Ffor every #2 of total income over
OL,13,F#100,000, will remain unchanged.
OL,15,FI am also holding the lower rate of
OL,16,Fincome tax at 10% and the threshold of
OL,17,Fincome taxable at #6,500 for a single
OL,18,Fperson and #13,000 for a jointly
OL,19,Fassessed couple.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G3/7
