OL,3,CIncome tax to rise from 20% to 22% in
OL,4,Cthe Isle of Man
OL,6,F"Reluctantly, however, after exploring
OL,7,Fmy options for a balanced budget, I
OL,8,Fhave made the difficult decision to
OL,9,Fincrease the higher rate of income tax
OL,10,Ffrom 20% to 22%, ring fencing this
OL,11,Fextra income to support our NHS."
OL,13,FThe government is expected to spend
OL,14,F#1.3 billion over the next financial
OL,15,Fyear, which equates to #16,343 per
OL,16,Fperson.
