OL,4,Cthe Isle of Man
OL,6,FGovernment has also committed to
OL,7,Fspending #429m on capital projects
OL,8,Fover the next five years, with #101m
OL,9,Fput aside for the next financial year.
OL,11,FMuch of the government's finances has
OL,12,Fbeen reliant on the island's reserves
OL,13,Fsince the Covid-19 pandemic, with #98m
OL,14,Fexpected to be used over the next year.
OL,16,FMinister Allinson said: "We will need
OL,17,Fto use our reserves over the medium
OL,18,Fterm to protect our essential public
OL,19,Fservices, but that this need will
OL,20,Freduce to a much lower level in future
OL,21,Fyears.
