OL,3,CIncome tax to rise from 20% to 22% in
OL,4,Cthe Isle of Man
OL,6,F"Our invaluable reserves, which have
OL,7,Fprovided our nation with a cushion and
OL,8,Fthe stability to withstand the global
OL,9,Fevents of the last three years, have
OL,10,Falso suffered the effects of market
OL,11,Fvolatility."
OL,13,FHe concluded: "As I have already
OL,14,Fstated, we must protect our vital
OL,15,Fservices, however, in doing so we can
OL,16,Fno longer simply rely on reserves."
